@mrbeast I'm John Paul Masamba, a 23-year-old South African boxer on a journey to the Paris 2024 Olympics. My story is one of resilience, battling inner demons and opponents in the ring. Join me on this journey by supporting my training camp in the United Kingdom and my Olympic dreams.

I competed at the Olympic trials in Dakar, Senegal, from September 9th to the 15th, and I proudly won a bronze medal, but it was not enough to secure an Olympic ticket. I was the only South African athlete who made it to the podium.

I'm determined to compete in the next trials, which will be held in Italy and Bangkok, where five slots will be given away for the Paris 2024 Olympic Games. Your support will be crucial in preparing for these competitions.

Support a 23-year-old like me in proving that, no matter the challenges, we can keep going and inspire others, while also bringing world-class skills back to South Africa's boxing community. Help me pursue my Olympic dream and earn a spot at the Paris2024Olympics
